main event: Three blinking lights were observed in the sky over Cincinnati, Ohio on April 9, 1960.
interesting points: The objects were only observed as blinking lights, and there was insufficient data to draw a firm conclusion about their identity.
The witness, a civilian, reported the sighting to the Air Force.
The Air Force requested the witness complete an additional report form to provide more information about the observation.
The sighting lasted for an unknown duration, but was initially observed at 9:15 AM.
The witness stated the objects did not exhibit any characteristic behavior of aircraft.
sighted object: three blinking lights in the sky
